tings%20in%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%2C%20Munger%2C%20since%20he%20stepped%20down%20from%20the%20top%20party%20post.%20Speaking%20at%20one%20of%20the%20meetings%20yesterday%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BReligion%20and%20faith%20are%20not%20for%20exhibition.%20I%20am%20a%20Hindu%20too%20and%20my%20faith%20is%20deep%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20show%20it%20like%20those%20from%20the%20BJP.%20Religious%20places%20are%20not%20sites%20for%20exhibition.%20They%20are%20being%20used%20to%20mislead%20people.%20The%20media%20is%20being%20put%20forward%20to%20spread%20falsehood%20through%20sponsored%20news%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20%26quot%3Bpredictions%20of%20the%20fall%20of%20Bihar%20government%20and%20JDU%20split%20are%20far%20from%20truth%26quot%3B.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Nitish%20Kumar-led%20alliance%20government%20is%20going%20strong%20in%20Bihar.%20In%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20we%20will%20fight%20together%20from%20the%20INDIA%20platform.%20Bihar%20will%20show%20the%20way%20for%20the%20farewell%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20(Prime%20Minister%20Narendra)%20Modi.%20The%20people%20have%20made%20up%20their%20minds%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Singh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Mr%20Singh%20stepped%20down%20as%20JDU%20chief%2C%20Bihar%20Chief%20Minister%20Nitish%20Kumar%20took%20over%20the%20post%20during%20the%20JDU's%20national%20executive%20meeting%20at%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Mr%20Singh%20has%20said%20he%20quit%20the%20top%20post%20owing%20to%20engagements%20in%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituency%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20claimed%20he%20was%20removed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20leader%20from%20Bihar%2C%20Shahnawaz%20Hussain%2C%20told%20news%20agency%20ANI%2C%20%26quot%3BNitish%20Kumar%20ji%20first%20made%20RCP%20Singh%20president%2C%20then%20Lalan%20Singh%20and%20now%20he%20himself%20has%20become%20president%20of%20JD%20(U).%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Singh%20has%20said%20he%20would%20sue%20media%20outfits%20publishing%20reports%20that%20he%20had%20plotted%20a%20rebellion%20against%20Nitish%20Kumar%20in%20favour%20of%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20leader%20Tejashwi%20Yadav.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20he%20said%20the%20reports%20in%20%26quot%3Bone%20major%20newspaper%20and%20some%20news%20channels%26quot%3B%20were%20%26quot%3Bcompletely%20misleading%2C%20false%20and%20aimed%20at%20tarnishing%20my%20reputation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704093120000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fg8s5jnho_lalan-singh-pti_625x300_01_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajiv-ranjan-singh-lalan-singh-nitish-kumar-im-a-hindu-too-but-jdu-ex-chief-slams-bjp-after-quitting-top-post-4779678%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20his%20first%20public%20meetings%20after%20quitting%20as%20party%20president%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20leader%20Rajiv%20Ranjan%20Singh%20has%20said%20he%20is%20a%20pious%20Hindu%20but%20does%20not%20%26quot%3Bexhibit%20it%20like%20those%20from%20BJP%26quot%3B.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajiv-ranjan-singh-lalan-singh-nitish-kumar-im-a-hindu-too-but-jdu-ex-chief-slams-bjp-after-quitting-top-post-4779678%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajiv-ranjan-singh-lalan-singh-nitish-kumar-im-a-hindu-too-but-jdu-ex-chief-slams-bjp-after-quitting-top-post-4779678%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Frajiv-ranjan-singh-lalan-singh-nitish-kumar-im-a-hindu-too-but-jdu-ex-chief-slams-bjp-after-quitting-top-post-4779678%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nobel%20laureate%20Yunus%20faces%20jail%20in%20Bangladesh%20court%20ruling%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704093022000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106442107%2Cimgsize-234952.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-faces-jail-in-bangladesh-court-ruling%2Farticleshow%2F106442111.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106442111.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-faces-jail-in-bangladesh-court-ruling%2Farticleshow%2F106442111.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-faces-jail-in-bangladesh-court-ruling%2Famp_articleshow%2F106442111.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Fnobel-laureate-muhammad-yunus-faces-jail-in-bangladesh-court-ruling%2Famp_articleshow%2F106442111.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22A%20Look%20at%20China%E2%80%99s%20Ambitious%20Spaceplane%20Missions%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01120225%2Fimage-1680.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20some%20years%20now%20China%20has%20been%20making%20innovative%20investments%20in%20the%20space%20domain.%20Apart%20from%20undertaking%20routine%20satellite%20launch%20missions%2C%20the%20country%20is%20undertaking%20missions%20which%20could%20possibly%20have%20both%20research%20and%20military%20utility.%20A%20Chinese%20spaceplane%2C%20dubbed%20as%20Shenlong%2C%20which%20is%20Chinese%20for%20%E2%80%98Divine%20Dragon%E2%80%99%2C%20is%20one%20such%20mission.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20China%20launched%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fspacenews.com%2Fchina-launches-mystery-reusable-spaceplane-for-third-time%2F%5C%22%3Ethird%20spaceplane%3C%2Fa%3E%20mission.%20Its%20first%20spaceplane%20mission%20in%20September%202020%20lasted%20only%20for%20two%20days.%20The%20second%20mission%2C%20which%20started%20from%20August%202022%20till%20May%202023%2C%20was%20operational%20for%20276%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20third%20mission%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thinkchina.sg%2Fchinas-strides-spaceflight-put-us-notice%5C%22%3Ewas%20launched%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20December%2019%2C%202023.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20known%20for%20how%20many%20days%20or%20years%20this%20mission%20will%20last.%20During%20the%20ongoing%20mission%2C%20China%20has%20deployed%20six%20%E2%80%98mysterious%20wingmen%E2%80%99%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20orbit%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fchinas-space-plane-deployed-6-mysterious-wingmen-in-orbit-claims-amateur-astronomer-4712071%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20suggest%20that%20these%20missions%20could%20be%20testing%20satellite%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurasiantimes.com%2Fus-india-caught-off-guard-as-china-tests-swarm-drone-technology-that-can-outflank-enemy-defences%2F%5C%22%3Eswarm%20technology.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceplanes%20are%20not%20a%20new%20concept.%20Research%20and%20several%20debates%20have%20been%20held%20on%20this%20subject%20since%20the%20early%201960s.%20Apart%20from%20the%20US%20and%20USSR%20(now%20Russia)%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20France%2C%20and%20Japan%20have%20undertaken%20such%20missions%20in%20experiment%20mode%20or%20as%20fully%20operational%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20spaceplane%20could%20be%20viewed%20as%20a%20combination%20of%20aircraft%20and%20spacecraft.%20It%20flies%20(or%20glides)%20like%20an%20aircraft%20within%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%20and%20operates%20as%20a%20spacecraft%20in%20outer%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20appears%20that%20the%20first%20two-day%20mission%20launched%20by%20China%20was%20more%20like%20a%20prototype%20mission%2C%20and%20the%20second%20mission%2C%20which%20lasted%20for%20around%20nine%20months%2C%20could%20have%20given%20China%20the%20necessary%20confidence%20to%20plan%20more%20such%20missions.%20During%20the%20second%20mission%2C%20the%20spaceplane%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.yahoo.com%2Fchinas-mysterious-spaceplane-raises-orbit-180000405.html%3Fguccounter%3D1%26guce_referrer%3DaHR0cHM6Ly90aGV3aXJlLmluLw%26guce_referrer_sig%3DAQAAAERzdAM2o3LsfJMiKuhuhSJZibN1l5p1j6Quxz2-V0mpSO2D6M0-orYhCEfECg0OFZEvn-J7NLioymYNxSu4414lfrzw8TvTawmFCqYJOLREPHoDQyX7gi7q19Dkrj1810RAKDCWju6LjJ9P2HsUpRYDgEP69fik1nk3ZvLUfU0U%5C%22%3Eperformed%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20orbit-raising%20maneuver%20on%20August%2025%2C%202022.%20It%20was%20in%20a%20near-circular%20597%20by%20608-kilometre%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20indicates%20that%20China%20has%20developed%20a%20capability%20to%20position%20a%20craft%20in%20different%20orbits%20in%20a%20single%20mission.%20This%20reusable%20craft%20has%20been%20developed%20by%20the%20China%20Aerospace%20Science%20and%20Technology%20Corporation%20(CASC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20three%20missions%20demonstrate%20China%E2%80%99s%20success%20in%20developing%20reusable%20spaceplane%20technology%20and%20improved%20capabilities%20in%20the%20arenas%20like%20heat%20shields%20and%20landing%20equipment.%20Some%20experts%20believe%20that%20since%20this%20plane%20had%20demonstrated%20the%20capability%20of%20very%20high-speed%20re-entry%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20atmosphere%2C%20possibly%20this%20could%20assist%20China%E2%80%99s%20hypersonic%20missile%20program.%20However%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20mention%20that%20China%20already%20has%20a%20reasonably%20well-established%20hypersonic%20weapons%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20earlier%20mentioned%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20recent%20spaceplane%20has%20deployed%20six%20%E2%80%98mysterious%20wingmen%E2%80%99%20into%20the%20Earth%E2%80%99s%20orbit.%20Currently%2C%20these%20objects%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wionews.com%2Fworld%2Fus-plans-to-beat-china-in-launch-of-secret-space-plane-spacex-foils-plan-670084%5C%22%3Ebeing%20tracked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20US%20Space%20Force.%20For%20ease%20of%20tracking%2C%20they%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.space.com%2Fchina-space-plane-depoyed-mystery-objects%5C%22%3Ehave%20named%3C%2Fa%3E%20them%20as%20OBJECT%20A%20through%20F.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20them%20are%20in%20a%20similar%20orbit%20and%20are%20known%20to%20have%20moved%20closer%20to%20each%20other.%20Most%20of%20them%20are%20emitting%20different%20types%20of%20signals.%20They%20are%20expected%20to%20make%20several%20close%20approaches%20with%20each%20other%20in%20future.%20During%20earlier%20missions%2C%20too%2C%20Chinese%20spaceplanes%20had%20released%20some%20objects%20in%20space%2C%20which%20were%20also%20tracked%20by%20the%20US%20Space%20Force.%20Experts%20believe%20that%20this%20time%2C%20the%20six%20objects%20show%20a%20different%20radio%20behaviour%20in%20comparison%20with%20the%20objects%20released%20during%20the%20earlier%20two%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPossibly%2C%20the%20technology%20used%20by%20China%20to%20design%20and%20develop%20these%20spaceplanes%20is%20similar%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.popularmechanics.com%2Fmilitary%2Fa46190887%2Fx-37b-vs-shenlong-spaceplane%2F%5C%22%3EBoeing%20X-37B%3C%2Fa%3E%20(the%20secretive%20US%20spaceplane).%20This%20craft%20is%20a%20robotic%20autonomous%20vehicle%20and%20has%20been%20in%20NASA%E2%80%99s%20service%20since%202010.%20NASA%20and%20the%20US%20Space%20Force%20have%20already%20undertaken%20six%20launches%20of%20this%20vehicle.%20The%20US%20has%20developed%20two%20vehicles%20in%20this%20category%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20their%20missions%20stayed%20in%20space%20for%20a%20period%20of%20around%20two%20years.%20The%20last%20mission%2C%20which%20got%20back%20to%20Earth%20during%20November%202022%2C%20was%20out%20there%20for%20908%20days.%20These%20missions%20were%20at%20an%20orbit%20of%20around%20400%20km.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20US%20administration%20has%20been%20totally%20silent%20about%20the%20rationale%20behind%20undertaking%20these%20missions.%20Possibly%2C%20they%20could%20have%20conducted%20on-orbit%20science%20and%20military-related%20experiments%20during%20the%20long%20stay%20of%20these%20crafts%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20obvious%20that%20both%20the%20US%20and%20the%20Chinese%20agencies%20must%20have%20gathered%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20atmospheric%2C%20space%20weather-related%20and%20reconnaissance%20data%20(continuous%20data%20sets).%20Such%20data%20could%20be%20utilised%20for%20the%20development%20of%20various%20mathematical%20models.%20It%20is%20known%20that%20the%20worth%20of%20various%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20algorithms%20depends%20much%20on%20data%20inputs%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20such%20humongous%20data%20could%20help%20these%20nations%20in%20fine-tuning%20their%20AI-based%20scientific%20and%20military%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20conducting%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.dtic.mil%2Fsti%2Fcitations%2FADA468025%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520January%252011%252C%25202007%252C%2520the%2Cconcerns%2520about%2520more%2520space%2520debris.%5C%22%3Eanti-satellite%20test%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ASAT)%20during%202007%2C%20China%20is%20found%20to%20have%20systematically%20developed%20its%20counter-space%20program.%20The%20messaging%20behind%20this%20test%20was%20very%20clear%3A%20China%20would%20not%20hesitate%20to%20take%20the%20warfare%20to%20outer%20space.%20After%20this%20test%2C%20concerns%20were%20raised%20over%20China%E2%80%99s%20reckless%20creation%20of%20space%20debris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202023%20witnessed%20China%20undertaking%20various%20important%20space%20missions.%20For%20instance%2C%20it%20invested%20in%20some%20basic%20technologies%20which%20have%20been%20in%20use%20for%20centuries%2C%20such%20as%20high-altitude%20balloon%20missions.%20In%20early%202023%2C%20a%20Chinese%20balloon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fchinese-spy-balloon-spotted-over-us-says-pentagon%5C%22%3Ehad%20intruded%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20US%20airspace%2C%20and%20in%20December%2C%20a%20balloon%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fasia-pacific%2Ftaiwan-detected-two-chinese-balloons-crossing-taiwan-strait-sunday-defence-2023-12-18%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20detected%3C%2Fa%3E%20moving%20across%20the%20Taiwan%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20spaceplanes%20to%20balloons%2C%20China%20has%20been%20using%20a%20range%20of%20technologies%20for%20reconnaissance%2C%20undertaking%20experimentation%20(possibly%20of%20military%20relevance)%20and%20data%20generation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20India%2C%20some%20decades%20ago%2C%20debates%20were%20going%20on%20in%20the%20Defence%20Research%20and%20Development%20Organisation%20(DRDO)%20circles%20over%20the%20development%20of%20a%20spaceplane%20and%20a%20project%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdefenceforumindia.com%2Fthreads%2Fhypersonic-vehicles-scramjets.155%2F%5C%22%3Ecalled%3C%2Fa%3E%20AVATAR%20(Aerobic%20Vehicle%20for%20Hypersonic%20Aerospace%20Transportation).%20Possibly%2C%20the%20idea%20was%20to%20develop%20a%20system%20for%20undertaking%20low-cost%20military%20and%20commercial%20satellite%20launches.%20Satellite%20swarm%20technologies%20have%20great%20scientific%20and%20strategic%20potential%20and%20now%20the%20time%20has%20come%20for%20India%20to%20take%20the%20projects%20like%20AVATAR%20to%20its%20logical%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAjey%20Lele%20researches%20space%20issues%20and%20is%20the%20author%20of%20the%20book%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EInstitutions%20That%20Shaped%20Modern%20India%3A%20ISRO%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704092418000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01120225%2Fimage-1680.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fspace%2Fa-look-at-chinas-ambitious-spaceplane-missions%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%2