3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EImpacts%20on%20Amazon%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EGarrison%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etold%20BI%20that%20these%20tactics%20were%20a%20way%20to%20manage%20head%20count%20at%20Amazon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-rto-cross-country-move-worker-quit-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%20software%20development%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20was%20asked%20to%20move%20across%20the%20US%2C%20from%20New%20York%20to%20Seattle%2C%20for%20RTO%20previously%20shared%20the%20same%20sentiment%20with%20Business%20Insider.%20After%20nearly%20four%20years%20at%20the%20company%2C%20the%20employee%20took%20a%20%24203%2C000%20pay%20cut%20by%20forfeiting%20unvested%20stocks%20solely%20because%20of%20Amazon's%20RTO%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20was%20going%20to%20surmise%2C%20I%20would%20think%20part%20of%20it%20is%20reducing%20head%20count%20without%20doing%20further%20layoffs%2C%20because%20that%20signals%20bad%20things%20to%20shareholders%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20manager%2C%20who%20requested%20to%20be%20anonymous%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20December%205%20X%20post%2C%20Merritt%20Baer%2C%20a%20former%20AWS%20employee%2C%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20sheer%20number%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-aws-employees-quitting-over-rto-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAWS%20resignations%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20last%20week%20is%20stunning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Rob%20Munoz%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20Amazon%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20company%20has%20been%20%26quot%3Brepeatedly%20been%20clear%20about%20what%20drove%20our%20decision%20on%20RTO%2C%20and%20these%20inaccurate%20and%20misleading%20anonymous%20anecdotes%20just%20aren't%20factual.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20February%2C%20we%20shared%20with%20employees%20that%20we'd%20be%20asking%20them%20to%20start%20coming%20into%20the%20office%20three%20or%20more%20days%20per%20week%20beginning%20in%20May%20because%20we%20believe%20it%20would%20yield%20the%20best%20long-term%20results%20for%20our%20customers%2C%20business%2C%20and%20culture.%20And%20it%20has.%20With%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20employees%20in%20the%20office%20more%20frequently%2C%20there's%20more%20energy%2C%20connection%2C%20and%20collaboration%2C%20and%20we're%20hearing%20that%20from%20employees%20and%20the%20businesses%20that%20surround%20our%20offices%2C%26quot%3B%20Munoz%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20software%20development%20manager%20who%20took%20the%20%24203%2C000%20pay%20cut%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20hadn't%20shown%20any%20evidence%20that%20productivity%20had%20decreased%20working%20from%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarrison%20acknowledged%20in%20his%20blog%20that%20the%20mass%20layoffs%20this%20year%20only%20impacted%20about%201.7%25%20of%20Amazon%20employees.%20Still%2C%20the%20RTO%20initiative%20and%20layoffs%20have%20caused%20many%20teams%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bemaciated%26quot%3B%20and%20may%20make%20the%20company%20less%20agile%20to%20innovate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20explained%20how%2C%20for%20years%2C%20Amazon's%20organizational%20approach%20was%20known%20as%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocs.aws.amazon.com%2Fwhitepapers%2Flatest%2Fintroduction-devops-aws%2Ftwo-pizza-teams.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo-pizza%20teams%3C%2Fa%3E.%26quot%3B%20Jeff%20Bezos%20said%20that%20the%20idea%20was%20%26quot%3Bto%20create%20teams%20that%20are%20no%20larger%20than%20can%20be%20fed%20by%20two%20pizzas.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20people%20are%20expensive%2C%20and%20Amazon%20appears%20to%20be%20shifting%20to%20a%20more%20%26quot%3Bcentralized%26quot%3B%20organization%2C%20Garrison%20said%2C%20in%20which%20a%20bigger%20team%20with%20a%20pool%20of%20expertise%20is%20created%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Beveryone%20borrows%20time%20from%20that%20centralized%20pool.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20downside%20of%20that%20is%20you%20have%20to%20wait%20in%20line%20to%20get%20an%20expert%20on%20something%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGarrison%20told%20BI%20that%20he%20would%20love%20to%20get%20a%20severance%20package%20but%20has%20since%20lost%20all%20expectations%20of%20getting%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20said%20he%20felt%20compelled%20to%20write%20his%20blog%20post%20so%20that%20he%20could%20speak%20for%20other%20lower-level%20Amazon%20employees%20who%20have%20been%20stuck%20in%20similar%20situations%20but%20might%20not%20have%20enough%20experience%20to%20quit%20their%20jobs%20or%20make%20a%20lot%20of%20noise.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWith%20the%20job%20market%20the%20way%20it%20is%2C%20they%20don't%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20connections%2C%26quot%3B%20Garrison%20said.%20%26quot%3BI've%20been%20in%20technology%20for%2020%20years.%20I'm%20going%20to%20be%20OK.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20posting%20his%20blog%20on%20Saturday%2C%20Garrison%20said%20he%20received%20messages%20from%20people%20across%20the%20company%20who%20said%20his%20post%20resonated%20with%20their%20position.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20haven't%20had%20a%20single%20person%20at%20Amazon%20who%20said%20I%20was%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20Garrison%20said.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20single%20one%20of%20them%20was%20like%2C%20'Yep%2C%20this%20is%20exactly%20what%20we've%20been%20living%20through%20and%20it%20sucks.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-amazon-employee-aws-quiet-firing-remote-work-severance-package-2023-12%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704087312000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659240041c5c7b8c9a0d1edd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsenior-amazon-employee-aws-quiet-firing-remote-work-severance-package-2023-12%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Justin%20Garrison%