ctory.%20The%20responsibility%20to%20carry%20forward%20the%20success%20of%202023%20now%20rests%20on%20Akshay%20Kumar%2C%20Ajay%20Devgn%2C%20and%20Hrithik%20Roshan.%20Exhibitor%20Akshaye%20Rathi%20believes%20it's%20time%20for%20the%20next%20generation%20of%20superstars%20to%20take%20over%20and%20ensure%20the%20Box%20Office%20continues%20to%20churn.%20While%20the%20Khans%20have%20no%20releases%2C%20the%20Telugu%20industry%20has%20big-ticket%20pan-India%20releases.%202024%20might%20see%20Akshay%20Kumar%20taking%20the%20center%20stage%20with%20three%20significant%20releases%2C%20making%20it%20his%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fwith-no-khan-movies-for-2024-will-next-gen-of-superstars-repeat-2023-box-office-successes%2Farticleshow%2F106432894.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Proxy%20or%20Power%3A%20A%20Grand%20Strategy%20for%20India%20in%20a%20Changing%20World%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01095452%2FUntitled-design.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20article%20has%20been%20extracted%20from%20the%20Matin%20Zuberi%20memorial%20lecture%20delivered%20by%20the%20author%20at%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20University%20on%20December%207%2C%202023.%20The%20full%20lecture%20is%20available%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vifindia.org%2Farticle%2F2023%2Fdecember%2F15%2FForgotten-Dimensions-of-Strategy-Russia-Ukraine-War-Lessons-for-India%5C%22%3E%20%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3Ehere%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20our%20daily%20lives%2C%20we%20all%20understand%20strategy%20broadly%20as%20getting%20things%20done.%20In%20the%20life%20of%20countries%2C%20matters%20of%20state%2C%20so%20to%20speak%2C%20strategy%20is%20more%20complex.%20National%20objectives%20differ%3B%20the%20means%20to%20achieve%20them%20are%20dissimilar%20and%20the%20international%20environment%20is%20often%20contested.%20There%20is%20the%20ever-present%20spectre%20of%20use%20or%20threat%20of%20use%20of%20force%2C%20which%20is%20the%20key%20characteristic%20that%20sets%20strategic%20studies%20apart%20from%20other%20disciplines.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20strategic%20instruments%20are%20impersonal%2C%20strategic%20decisions%20are%20not.%20These%20are%20made%20by%20individuals%20in%20positions%20of%20leadership%20that%20affect%20the%20fate%20of%20millions%20%E2%80%93%20for%20there%20is%20no%20human%20enterprise%20more%20consequential%20than%20the%20macabre%20dance%20of%20death%20and%20destruction%20on%20the%20highway%20of%20war.%20No%20war%20is%20good%20if%20it%20is%20avoidable.%20But%20lost%20wars%20are%20dreadful%2C%20for%20they%20inflict%20on%20the%20defeated%20not%20just%20the%20destruction%20wrought%20by%20battle%20but%20also%20the%20harsh%20penalties%20of%20peace%20arising%20from%20defeat.%20Good%20tactics%20enable%20good%20strategy%2C%20but%20successful%20strategy%20is%20one%20that%20fulfils%20the%20objectives%20of%20policy%20and%20remains%20bound%20by%20its%20limitations%20%E2%80%93%20both%20in%20terms%20of%20ambition%20and%20the%20means%20available%20for%20its%20accomplishment.%20In%20the%20pitiless%20world%20of%20strategy%2C%20high%20ambition%20backed%20by%20low%20capability%20is%20a%20sin%20without%20salvation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGrand%20strategy%2C%20one%20of%20the%20pillars%20of%20statecraft%20%E2%80%93%20which%20readers%20of%20Kautilya%20would%20be%20familiar%20with%20%E2%80%93%20considers%20not%20just%20military%20but%20non-military%20means.%20Grand%20strategy%20is%20the%20key%20to%20keeping%20a%20balance%20between%20means%20and%20ends%20and%20of%20seeking%20objectives%20within%20capabilities.%20It%20determines%20not%20only%20how%20to%20fight%20but%20also%20when%20to%20fight%20%E2%80%93%20for%20there%20are%20times%20when%20it%20is%20more%20prudent%20to%20undertake%20peacetime%20competition%20rather%20than%20seek%20military%20conflict.%20When%20to%20end%20a%20war%20is%20often%20as%20critical%20as%20when%20to%20start%20one.%20The%20rise%20of%20great%20powers%20is%20often%20a%20function%20of%20the%20success%20of%20their%20grand%20strategy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EForgotten%20dimensions.%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%201979%2C%20Michael%20Howard%2C%20Oxford%20University%E2%80%99s%20foremost%20war%20historian%2C%20wrote%20a%20seminal%20article%20in%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EForeign%20Affairs%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20titled%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farchive.ph%2FHFSaN%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CForgotten%20Dimensions%20of%20Strategy%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ein%20which%2C%20after%20a%20majestic%20survey%20of%20war%20in%20the%20preceding%20three%20centuries%2C%20he%20identified%20four%20dimensions%20along%20which%20all%20wars%20are%20conducted%20%E2%80%93%20the%20operational%2C%20the%20logistical%2C%20the%20social%2C%20and%20the%20technological.%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20under%20different%20circumstances%2C%20one%20or%20another%20of%20these%20dimensions%20would%20dominate%20and%20determine%20war%20outcomes.%20Prof%20Howard%20was%20writing%20at%20the%20height%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20when%20a%20relatively%20stable%20geopolitical%20balance%20acted%20as%20a%20firm%20foundation%20for%20the%20operationalisation%20of%20nuclear%20deterrence%20and%20its%20associated%20ecosystem%20of%20arms%20control%20and%20non-proliferation.%20The%20purpose%20of%20that%20article%20was%20to%20warn%20against%20the%20dangers%20of%20excessive%20dependence%20on%20the%20technological%20dimensions%20of%20war%20%E2%80%93%20in%20particular%2C%20nuclear%20war%2C%20to%20the%20exclusion%20of%20the%20other%20three.%20Were%20Michael%20Howard%20to%20write%20the%20article%20today%2C%20I%20would%20expect%20that%20he%20would%20add%20a%20fifth%20dimension%20%E2%80%93%20geopolitics%20%E2%80%93%20the%20renewed%20geopolitical%20competition%20between%20the%20big%20powers%20and%20the%20consequent%20weakening%20and%20fragmentation%20of%20deterrence%20in%20relations%20amongst%20them%2C%20which%20has%20led%20to%20the%20current%20lawlessness%20in%20the%20international%20system.%20This%20is%20where%20we%20turn%20to%20the%20ongoing%20conflict%20between%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-ukraine-russia-criticise%5C%22%3EWhy%20Is%20India%20Unable%20to%20Criticise%20the%20Country%20That%20Has%20Invaded%20Ukraine%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ELost%20opportunities%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20represents%20a%20failure%20of%20big%20power%20deterrence%20on%20account%20of%20miscalculations%20on%20questions%20of%20capability%2C%20credibility%2C%20and%20communication%20on%20part%20of%20both%20Russia%20and%20the%20United%20States.%20The%20active%20phase%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%20is%20now%20well%20into%20its%20second%20year.%20Since%202014%2C%20when%20an%20insurrection%20in%20Kyiv%20unseated%20the%20incumbent%20president%2C%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20were%20tense%20but%20subsequent%20opportunities%20for%20a%20peaceful%20resolution%20receded%20as%20Ukraine%20swing%20decisively%20towards%20the%20West.%20War%20was%20not%20inevitable%20but%20opportunities%20for%20peace%20were%20lost%20by%20both%20sides%20%E2%80%93%20t%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fepicenter.wcfia.harvard.edu%2Fblog%2Fthrough-ashes-minsk-agreements%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%202015%20Minsk%20accords%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20first%20year%20of%20President%20Zelenskyy%E2%80%99s%20term%2C%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2Fworld%2Flive-news%2Fbiden-putin-meeting-geneva-updates-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3EBiden-Putin%20Geneva%20Summit%20of%20June%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mid.ru%2Fen%2Fforeign_policy%2Fnews%2F1790809%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3ERussian%20proposals%20on%20European%20security%20of%20December%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20the%20abortive%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fresponsiblestatecraft.org%2Fukraine-peace-talks%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3ERussia-Ukraine%20peace%20talks%20of%20March%2FApril%202022%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20we%20now%20know%20from%20Ukrainian%20leaders%20were%20rejected%20on%20the%20advice%20of%20the%20UK%20and%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20Russia%20had%20to%20resort%20to%20use%20of%20force%20in%20its%20neighbourhood%20is%20not%20a%20measure%20of%20successful%20deterrence.%20That%20Ukraine%20miscalculated%20how%20its%20campaign%20to%20join%20NATO%20would%20not%20cross%20a%20red%20line%20that%20Russia%20had%20repeatedly%20articulated%20since%202007%20is%20not%20a%20measure%20of%20successful%20counter-deterrence.%20Ukraine%20took%20the%20risk%20of%20seeking%20the%20protection%20of%20a%20distant%20power%20to%20address%20its%20proximate%20security%20needs.%20The%20deeply%20embedded%20perception%20of%20Russian%20weakness%2C%20evident%20since%20the%201990s%2C%20on%20part%20of%20the%20US%20and%20its%20NATO%20allies%20masked%20from%20view%20the%20turnaround%20in%20Russian%20military%20strength%20under%20President%20Putin%20and%20its%20will%20to%20act%20militarily%20to%20protect%20its%20interests%20in%20Ukraine.%20The%20stage%20was%20set%20for%20a%20prolonged%20military%20confrontation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDoormats%20of%20history%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20have%20written%20elsewhere%20about%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20%E2%80%93including%2C%20I%20am%20a%20bit%20embarrassed%20to%20say%2C%20on%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fharsh-lessons-from-the-ukraine-crisis-7788045%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20first%20day%20of%20the%20war%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Eitself%2C%20with%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fone-year-of-ukraine-war-a-conflict-that-has-become-a-contest-of-will-between-russia-and-the-west-8463280%2F%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3Esubsequent%20piece%20a%20year%20later%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%93%20laying%20out%20a%20broken%20future%20for%20Ukraine%20with%20partial%20but%20permanent%20loss%20of%20territory%20to%20Russia%20and%20with%20the%20rump%20Ukraine%20joining%20NATO.%20Let%20me%20explain%20myself%2C%20via%20the%20five%20dimensions%20of%20strategy%20enumerated%20above.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20now%20a%20proxy%20war%20between%20Russia%20and%20the%20West.%20While%20the%20military%20conflict%20has%20been%20confined%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20southern%20Russia%2C%20and%20the%20Black%20Sea%20area%2C%20the%20economic%2C%20energy%2C%20informational%20and%20cyber%20dimensions%20have%20given%20it%20a%20global%20scale.%20Like%20all%20proxies%2C%20the%20fate%20of%20Ukraine%20is%20no%20longer%20in%20its%20own%20hands%20but%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20wavering%20American%20strategic%20benevolence%20and%20uncertain%20European%20support.%20There%20have%20been%20proxies%20in%20the%20past%20and%20there%20will%20be%20more%20in%20the%20future%2C%20but%20they%20all%20meet%20the%20same%20fate.%20For%20in%20geopolitical%20conflict%20involving%20the%20big%20powers%2C%20proxies%20are%20the%20doormats%20of%20history.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20operational%20terms%2C%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20desire%20for%20a%20quick%20and%20decisive%20blow%20against%20Kyiv%20in%20the%20early%20months%20of%20the%20war%20was%20a%20stunning%20failure.%20The%20fighting%20ability%20of%20Ukrainian%20units%20trained%20to%20NATO%20standards%20since%202016%20compelled%20Russian%20withdrawals%20in%20northern%20and%20north-eastern%20Ukraine.%20The%20societal%20dimension%20also%20held%20up%20%E2%80%93%20though%20over%2010%20million%20people%20fled%20as%20refuges%20to%20Russia%20and%20Europe.%20President%20Zelenskyy%20was%20able%20to%20rally%20his%20country%20together%2C%20undertake%20successive%20mobilisations%20and%20conduct%20successful%20operations%20until%20September%202022%20when%20Ukrainian%20forces%20reached%20the%20peak%20of%20their%20fighting%20capacity%2C%20having%20made%20advances%20in%20Kherson%2C%20Kharkiv%20and%20Sumy%20areas.%20Military%20support%20from%20the%20US%20and%20NATO%20of%20advanced%20weaponry%20added%20a%20new%20technological%20dimension%20to%20its%20fighting%20capacity.%20By%20the%20winter%20of%202022%20the%20war%20had%20settled%20into%20a%20stalemate%20as%20none%20of%20the%20five%20dimensions%20%E2%80%93%20operational%2C%20logistical%2C%20technological%2C%20societal%2C%20or%20geopolitical%20were%20able%20to%20provide%20a%20decisive%20outcome%20to%20either%20side.%20Russia%20was%20too%20weak%20to%20win%2C%20and%20Ukraine%20was%20too%20strong%20to%20lose.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20in%20war%2C%20as%20in%20life%2C%20time%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20stand%20still.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECoconut%20grater%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20its%20second%20year%2C%20the%20stalemated%20war%20has%20turned%20gradually%20in%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20favour.%20US%20and%20EU%20sanctions%20against%20Russia%20were%20predicated%20on%20crippling%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20will%20and%20ability%20to%20conduct%20a%20prolonged%20war.%20Contrary%20to%20western%20expectations%2C%20the%20Russian%20defence%20industry%20has%20bounced%20back%2C%20with%20a%20huge%20hike%20in%20defence%20expenditure%20under%20conditions%20of%20better-than-expected%20but%20still%20modest%20economic%20growth.%20The%20Russian%20military%2C%20like%20in%20all%20wars%2C%20has%20been%20adept%20at%20learning%20from%20its%20past%20mistakes.%20Having%20blunted%20the%20fighting%20capacity%20of%20the%20virulently%20far%20right%20anti-Russian%20units%20in%20the%20Ukrainian%20armed%20forces%2C%20including%20the%20AZOV%20battalion%20in%20Mariupol%2C%20Russia%20has%20systematically%20reduced%20Ukrainian%20fighting%20power%20in%20battles%20around%20Bakhmut%20and%20now%20in%20Avdeevka.%20Like%20a%20coconut%20grater%2C%20strong%20Russian%20defences%20have%20decimated%20Ukrainian%20forces.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20operational%20terms%2C%20the%20war%20has%20moved%20from%20one%20of%20manoeuvre%20to%20that%20of%20attrition.%20This%20is%20due%20to%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20ISR%20revolution%20disrobing%20battlefields%20of%20stealth%20or%20cover%20and%20the%20proliferation%20of%20drones%20and%20standoff%20weapons%20which%20can%20hit%20at%20will%20forces%20out%20in%20the%20open%2C%20making%20offensive%20operations%20costly%20in%20term%20of%20equipment%20and%20manpower.%20Ukraine%20is%20also%20running%20short%20of%20fighting%20manpower-%20with%20its%20average%20officer%20age%20in%20the%2040s.%20With%20an%20operational%20stalemate%20compounded%20by%20societal%20and%20logistical%20weakness%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20now%20desperately%20searching%20for%20a%20technological%20edge%20that%20could%20restore%20balance%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20which%20it%20can%20only%20get%20from%20the%20West%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20is%20related%20to%20the%20geopolitical%20dimensions%20of%20the%20war.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k-300x200.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F02%2F20165942%2F51905521463_0600c20141_k-1024x683.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-641263%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20protest%20against%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine.%20Photo%3A%20pix-4-2-day%2FFlickr%20CC%20BY%20NC%20ND%202.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFickle%20affections%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20President%20Putin%E2%80%99s%20nuclear%20warnings%20to%20the%20West%20not%20to%20supply%20advanced%20weaponry%20to%20Ukraine%20went%20largely%20unheeded%2C%20the%20West%20is%20now%20worried%20about%20the%20consequences%20of%20a%20major%20escalation%20with%20Russia.%20A%20Ukraine-fatigue%20has%20set%20in%20Europe.%20There%20is%20a%20fundamental%20churn%20in%20its%20political%20economy%20whose%20full%20implications%20are%20only%20beginning%20to%20become%20apparent%2C%20with%20two%20critical%20elements%20%E2%80%93%20a%20resentment%20against%20sacrificing%20more%20for%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20war%20and%20a%20resentment%20against%20American%20domination%20over%20European%20energy%20and%20security%20policies.%20In%20America%2C%20the%20political%20ground%20has%20shifted%20somewhat%20with%20a%20Republican%20pushback%20in%20an%20upcoming%20election%20year.%20US%20focus%20towards%20Israel%20following%20the%20crisis%20in%20Palestine%20since%20early%20October%20has%20struck%20a%20body%20blow%20to%20Ukraine%20as%20the%20top%20spot%20for%20American%20attention.%20Thus%2C%20with%20the%20logistical%20and%20geopolitical%20dimensions%20of%20the%20war%20shifting%20in%20its%20favour%2C%20perhaps%20irreversibly%2C%20Russia%20may%20be%20better%20placed%20by%20next%20year%20to%20dictate%20the%20terms%20of%20a%20peace%20settlement%20than%20it%20has%20been%20since%20the%20commencement%20of%20the%20war%20in%202022.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20will%20of%20course%20be%20a%20contested%20peace%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20US%20and%20EU%20will%20continue%20with%20a%20tight%20sanctions%20regime%20as%20well%20as%20the%20tight%20geopolitical%20encirclement%20of%20Russia%20on%20its%20periphery.%20Russia%20would%20seek%20a%20peace%20whose%20primary%20aim%20would%20be%20to%20ensure%20that%20Ukraine%20would%20not%20launch%20a%20war%20of%20revanchism%20to%20take%20back%20Donbass%20or%20become%20a%20forward%20base%20for%20American%20or%20NATO%20forces.%20Success%20would%20depend%20on%20the%20scale%20of%20its%20military%20victory%20or%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20state.%20Ukraine%20is%20learning%20the%20hard%20way%20the%20risks%20of%20entrusting%20national%20security%20to%20the%20fickle%20affections%20of%20distant%20mentors.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENot%20an%20era%20of%20war%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20diplomatic%20approach%20to%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20has%20been%20one%20of%20pragmatic%20prudence%2C%20even%20while%20recognising%20the%20unpredictable%20nature%20of%20war%20gains%20in%20an%20interconnected%20world%2C%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20saying%20that%20it%20is%20not%20an%20era%20of%20war.%20Our%20diplomacy%20achieved%20the%20difficult%20task%20of%20bringing%20back%20over%2020%2C000%20Indian%20students%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20many%20of%20them%20from%20active%20war%20zones.%20While%20India%20has%20not%20condemned%20Russia%20for%20the%20invasion%2C%20it%20has%20highlighted%20its%20broader%20consequences%20%E2%80%93%20on%20energy%2C%20food%20and%20fertilisers%20and%20the%20global%20disequilibrium%20that%20the%20war%20has%20produced%20and%20of%20particular%20concern%20to%20the%20Global%20South.%20Russia%2C%20our%20long-standing%20strategic%20partner%2C%20may%20finally%20prevail%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20the%20war%20has%20placed%20it%20on%20the%20back%20foot%20at%20least%20for%20the%20next%20decade.%20Another%20of%20our%20close%20strategic%20partners%20%E2%80%93%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20is%20now%20an%20overextended%20global%20power%2C%20attempting%20dual%20containment%20of%20Russia%20and%20China%20and%20succeeding%20in%20neither.%20This%20has%20provided%20a%20geopolitical%20sweet%20spot%20for%20China%2C%20which%20it%20is%20poised%20to%20exploit%2C%20despite%20the%20considerable%20downturn%20in%20its%20economic%20growth%20and%20instability%20in%20the%20ranks%20of%20its%20governing%20elite.%20In%20this%20triangular%20geopolitical%20equation%2C%20China%20has%20gained%20more%20than%20the%20other%20two.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhat%20then%20are%20the%20takeaways%20for%20India%3F%20While%20Indian%20diplomacy%20has%20shown%20considerable%20skill%20in%20navigating%20a%20turbulent%20international%20system%2C%20including%20the%20remarkable%20success%20of%20the%20Delhi%20G20%20summit%2C%20the%20underlying%20geopolitical%20trends%20are%20deeply%20troubling.%20A%20breakdown%20in%20deterrence%20equations%20%E2%80%93%20with%20nuclear%20deterrence%20no%20longer%20capable%20of%20deterring%20big%20power%20conflict%20in%20the%20conventional%2C%20cyber%20or%20space%20domains%2C%20and%20the%20weaponisation%20of%20global%20interdependence%20radiating%20instability%20and%20unpredictability%20into%20non-military%20sectors%20globally%2C%20are%20key%20trends.%20International%20law%2C%20public%20opinion%20or%20even%20public%20conscience%20are%20now%20weak%20filters%20against%20conflict.%20There%20is%20wilful%20disregard%20of%20the%20UN%20and%20of%20arms%20control%20agreements.%20In%20this%20age%20of%20growing%20lawlessness%2C%20old%20paradigms%20of%20interstate%20deterrence%20are%20breaking%20down%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20new%20actors%2C%20new%20technologies%20and%20new%20threats.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20what%20specific%20lessons%20can%20India%20take%20from%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20conflict%20and%20the%20broader%20international%20situation%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Frussia-ukraine-war-sitting-on-the-fence-cannot-be-a-sustainable-foreign-policy-for-india%5C%22%3ERussia-Ukraine%20War%3A%20Sitting%20on%20the%20Fence%20Cannot%20Be%20a%20Sustainable%20Foreign%20Policy%20for%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EProlonged%20wars%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOperationally%2C%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict%20portends%20the%20onset%20of%20prolonged%20wars%2C%20which%20count%20not%20on%20military%20defeat%20but%20national%20exhaustion%20of%20the%20enemy.%20While%20no%20two%20wars%20are%20alike%2C%20and%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20environment%20with%20China%20and%20Pakistan%20is%20vastly%20different%2C%20the%20general%20paradigm%20shift%20in%20warfare%20will%20have%20a%20long-term%20impact.%20With%20the%20ascendency%20of%20defence%20as%20compared%20to%20offence%2C%20and%20the%20elimination%20of%20surprise%20due%20to%20the%20ISR%20revolution%2C%20semi-permanent%20war%20preparedness%20would%20become%20the%20norm.%20This%20would%20require%20longer%20deployments%20and%20quicker%20rotations%20than%20in%20the%20past%2C%20which%20will%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20overall%20numbers%20of%20deployable%20armed%20forces.%20The%20possibility%20of%20a%20two-front%20war%20with%20both%20Pakistan%20and%20China%20is%20higher%20than%20in%20the%20past.%20India%20needs%20to%20prepare%20two%20different%20war%20fighting%20doctrines%20%E2%80%93%20for%20Chinese%20capabilities%20are%20vastly%20different%20from%20those%20of%20Pakistan%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20be%20prepared%20to%20execute%20them%20simultaneously.%20Prolonged%20wars%20also%20require%20logistics%20%E2%80%93%20stocks%2C%20reserves%2C%20and%20manufacturing%20potential%20of%20our%20domestic%20industry%20of%20a%20higher%20order%20as%20well%20as%20insulation%20against%20uncertain%20external%20supplies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESocietal%20changes%20would%20need%20to%20adapt%20to%20the%20new%20strategic%20requirements%20%E2%80%93%20higher%20educational%20standards%20for%20intake%20into%20our%20armed%20forces%20and%20an%20in-service%20retention%20pattern%20that%20would%20ensure%20sufficiently%20trained%20and%20experienced%20units%20that%20can%20maintain%20effective%20combat%20readiness%20for%20prolonged%20periods%20in%20a%20high-tech%20combat%20environment.%20This%20is%20not%20an%20easy%20task%20for%20countries%20moving%20from%20limitless%20peasantry%20to%20a%20middle-class%20aspiring%20youth%20in%20a%20fast-growing%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20terms%20of%20technology%2C%20we%20are%20witnessing%20the%20dawn%20of%20multidomain%20combat%20environments%20with%20unpredictable%20cross%20domain%20linkages%20%E2%80%93%20cyber%2C%20space%20and%20AI%20which%20are%20fundamentally%20transformative%20of%20future%20warfare.%20The%20fusion%20between%20the%20sensor%20and%20the%20striker%20in%20weapon%20systems%20will%20become%20tighter%20and%20faster%20than%20ever%20before.%20Technology%20is%20malleable%20thus%20making%20situational%20and%20doctrinal%20surprise%20likely%2C%20if%20we%20make%20the%20mistake%20of%20thinking%20that%20the%20opponent%20thinks%20like%20us.%20Prepare%20to%20be%20surprised%20but%20prepare%20to%20prevail.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EDosa%20batter%20with%20pizza%20dough%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20geopolitical%20dimension%20is%20now%20a%20critical%20reference%20point%20to%20calculate%20accurately%20the%20ebb%20and%20flow%20of%20international%20power.%20The%20role%20of%20diplomacy%20is%20vital%20%E2%80%93%20as%20the%20eyes%20and%20ears%20on%20a%20fast-changing%20world.%20Developing%20our%20own%20concepts%20is%20necessary%20as%20part%20of%20the%20change%20that%20we%20are%20witnessing%20and%20wish%20to%20influence.%20Building%20multipolarity%20with%20legacy%20concepts%20from%20the%20unipolar%20world%20would%20be%20like%20making%20dosa%20batter%20with%20pizza%20dough.%20Fit%20for%20purpose%20is%20measured%20by%20utility%20not%20familiarity.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDiplomacy%20can%20also%20play%20the%20role%20of%20a%20facilitator%20of%20access%20to%20the%20sinews%20of%20our%20national%20development%20%E2%80%93%20to%20capital%2C%20markets%2C%20technology%2C%20and%20the%20protection%20of%20our%20nationals%20abroad.%20While%20we%20are%20focused%20on%20maritime%20connectivity%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20continental%20access%20to%20mainland%20Eurasia%20is%20being%20challenged%20%E2%80%93%20by%20the%20extension%20of%20Chinese%20influence%20into%20Central%20Asia%2C%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%20Hence%2C%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20International%20North%E2%80%93South%20Transport%20Corridor%20(INSTC)%2C%20the%20Eastern%20Maritime%20Corridor%20(EMC)%20and%20the%20India%20Middle%20East%20Corridor%20(IMEC).%20Balancing%20our%20continental%20interests%20with%20that%20of%20our%20maritime%20interests%20is%20thus%20vitally%20important.%20How%20can%20India%20become%20a%20great%20power%20if%20we%20are%20geopolitically%20marginalised%20with%20limited%20land%20access%20on%20own%20continent%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGeopolitical%20conflict%20feeds%20not%20just%20on%20territories%20but%20also%20on%20technology.%20Given%20the%20pervasive%20securitisation%20of%20global%20interdependence%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20global%20supply%20chains%20constitute%20more%20than%2070%25%20of%20global%20trade%2C%20it%20is%20vital%20we%20have%20the%20best%20of%20relations%20with%20the%20United%20States%2C%20and%20the%20top%20technology%20companies%20which%20are%20now%20formidable%20global%20players%2C%20in%20their%20own%20right.%20As%20a%20global%20power%2C%20the%20US%20would%20seek%20tradeoffs%20consistent%20with%20its%20own%20global%20interests.%20Its%20current%20strategic%20predicament%20%E2%80%93%20a%20failing%20dual%20containment%20strategy%20against%20Russia%20and%20China%20along%20with%20a%20highly%20volatile%20Middle%20East%20involving%20the%20security%20of%20Israel%20%E2%80%93%20is%20stretching%20US%20global%20influence%20to%20its%20limits.%20In%20the%20words%20of%20one%20of%20its%20former%20defence%20secretaries%2C%20the%20US%20is%20now%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foreignaffairs.com%2Funited-states%2Frobert-gates-america-china-russia-dysfunctional-superpower%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98dysfunctional%20superpower%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20But%20it%20is%20regaining%20influence%20elsewhere%2C%20in%20Latin%20America%2C%20East%20Asia%20and%20in%20South%20Asia.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENotions%20of%20omnipotence%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20India%2C%20it%20is%20important%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20US%20for%20what%20it%20is%20%E2%80%93%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20largest%20economy%2C%20a%20pre-eminent%20technology%20and%20energy%20power%20but%20whose%20power%20projection%20capabilities%20are%20being%20increasingly%20constrained%20by%20a%20deeply%20divided%20domestic%20polity%2C%20which%20is%20reducing%20its%20ability%20to%20simultaneously%20pursue%20a%20welfare%20state%20at%20home%20and%20a%20warfare%20state%20abroad.%20This%20is%20driving%20in%20turn%20an%20unsustainable%20rise%20in%20national%20debt.%20The%20US%20of%20the%20coming%20decades%20will%20be%20different%20from%20the%20US%20we%20have%20known%20since%20the%20end%20of%20Cold%20War.%20Exaggerated%20notions%20of%20US%20omnipotence%20in%20global%20affairs%20that%20tend%20to%20sometimes%20colour%20our%20thinking%2C%20much%20like%20the%20notions%20that%20were%20unquestioningly%20held%20about%20Soviet%20omnipotence%20in%20the%201980s%2C%20would%20only%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20mutual%20disappointment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDiplomacy%20can%20also%20play%20the%20role%20of%20a%20compensator%20or%20force%20multiplier%2C%20in%20situations%20of%20power%20asymmetry%20that%20we%20now%20face%20with%20respect%20to%20China.%20Last%20year%2C%20China%E2%80%99s%20total%20global%20exports%20were%20the%20same%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP.%20China%20will%20be%20a%20formidable%20power%20in%20the%20coming%20decades%20and%20is%20showing%20the%20same%20proclivities%20for%20domination%20as%20hegemonic%20powers%20of%20the%20past.%20We%20should%20see%20China%20through%20our%20own%20prism%2C%20not%20one%20borrowed%20from%20others.%20Restoring%20credible%20military%20deterrence%20against%20China%20will%20enhance%20our%20ability%20to%20break%20the%20girdle%20that%20it%20seeks%20to%20build%20in%20our%20immediate%20neighbourhood.%20While%20our%20neighbourhood%20policy%20should%20be%20one%20of%20maximum%20possible%20economic%20accommodation%2C%20our%20red%20lines%20of%20no%20foreign%20military%20presence%20or%20bases%20on%20their%20soil%2C%20should%20be%20clearly%20understood%20by%20our%20neighbours.%20The%20Ukraine%20case%20shows%20that%20such%20attempts%20only%20bring%20grief%20to%20all%20concerned.%20Similarly%2C%20we%20need%20the%20naval%20capability%20and%20the%20doctrinal%20framework%20to%20retain%20predominance%20in%20the%20IOR.%20While%20friendly%20navies%20are%20welcome%2C%20a%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2FU.S.-Indo-Pacific-Strategy.pdf%5C%22%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Free%20and%20Open%E2%80%99%20Indo-Pacific%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Edoesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20region%20is%20a%20free-for-all%20%E2%80%98dharmshala%E2%80%99%20for%20foreign%20powers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EFallacy%20of%20external%20balancing%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20defence%20relations%20with%20the%20US%20and%20arrangements%20such%20as%20the%20Quad%20are%20useful%20and%20necessary%20balancing%20instruments%20to%20compensate%20for%20the%20regional%20power%20differential%20with%20China%2C%20but%20such%20mechanisms%20cannot%20wholly%20compensate%20for%20shortfalls%20in%20our%20economic%20or%20defence%20potentials.%20Those%20supporting%20the%20so-called%20external%20balancing%20strategy%20to%20fill%20these%20gaps%20only%20generate%20false%20hopes%20and%20expectations.%20There%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20a%20robust%20buildup%20of%20our%20own%20economic%20and%20military%20capabilities.%20Here%20too%2C%20Ukraine%20is%20a%20tragic%20example%20of%20the%20fate%20that%20awaits%20those%20willing%20to%20become%20proxies%20in%20big%20power%20conflicts.%20Living%20on%20borrowed%20money%20is%20not%20the%20same%20as%20living%20on%20borrowed%20military%20strength%20%E2%80%93%20the%20latter%20erodes%20strategic%20autonomy%20far%20deeper%20than%20the%20former.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOur%20bilateral%20defence%20cooperation%20with%20the%20US%20should%20include%20robust%20technology%20cooperation%2C%20for%20which%20the%20US-India%20initiative%20on%20Critical%20and%20Emerging%20Technology%20(iCET)%20offers%20a%20promising%20start%2C%20and%20coordination%20of%20our%20deterrence%20postures%20in%20the%20broader%20region%20provided%20the%20US%20embraces%20the%20objective%20of%20a%20strong%20and%20independent%20India%20as%20vital%20to%20its%20strategic%20interests.%20The%20US%20would%20naturally%20seek%20a%20tradeoff%20for%20such%20cooperation%20in%20terms%20of%20India%20committing%20to%20an%20alignment%20with%20its%20regional%20and%20global%20interests.%20On%20some%20issues%20these%20coincide%20and%20on%20some%20they%20don%E2%80%99t.%20Extracting%20sustained%20US%20support%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20interests%20under%20conditions%20of%20fluctuating%20demands%20on%20US%20resources%20for%20its%20extensive%20interests%20elsewhere%20will%20be%20a%20vexing%20and%20perhaps%20exhausting%20pre-occupation%20of%20our%20diplomacy.%20But%20we%20must%20make%20every%20possible%20effort%20to%20keep%20open%20partnership%20possibilities.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EStrong%20fences%20for%20strong%20partnerships%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20sustainability%20of%20our%20long-term%20relations%20with%20the%20US%20is%20not%20only%20a%20matter%20of%20convergence%20of%20interests%20but%20equally%20of%20an%20understanding%20of%20limits%20that%20both%20sides%20agree%20to%20respect.%20Strong%20fences%20make%20good%20neighbours%20but%20also%20strong%20partnerships.%20A%20durable%20understanding%20on%20limits%20would%20be%20an%20invaluable%20investment%20in%20friction-reduction%20and%20the%20best%20guarantee%20of%20a%20long%20term%20and%20sustainable%20partnership.%20Ukraine%20is%20an%20example%20of%20the%20thin%20line%20between%20partner%20and%20proxy%20and%20a%20lesson%20for%20any%20country%20wanting%20to%20become%20the%20Ukraine%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETo%20clarify%20matters%2C%20the%20US%20should%20embrace%20our%20strategic%20autonomy%20just%20as%20it%20accepted%20India%E2%80%99s%20independent%20nuclear%20deterrent%20as%20a%20positive%20factor%20for%20its%20own%20interests.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20practice%2C%20this%20would%20mean%20drawing%20a%20firm%20red%20line%20on%20the%20issue%20of%20integration%20of%20our%20defence%20forces%20with%20those%20of%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20either%20through%20interoperability%20or%20joint%20basing.%20Externally%2C%20it%20is%20important%20we%20engage%20but%20not%20get%20entangled%20in%20its%20global%20interests%20which%20are%20varied%20and%20liable%20to%20unilateral%20change.%20In%20short%2C%20for%20our%20relations%20with%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20coordination%20yes%3B%20integration%20no%3A%20engagement%20yes%2C%20entanglement%20no.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWithin%20these%20parameters%20there%20exists%20a%20vast%20universe%20of%20cooperation%20possibilities%20which%20are%20vital%20and%20necessary%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20security%20which%20may%20be%20pursued%20with%20full%20vigour%2C%20for%20there%20is%20no%20other%20relationship%20that%20it%20is%20more%20important%20for%20India%20to%20get%20right%20than%20that%20with%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EContinental%20Eurasia%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERussia%20will%20remain%20important%20for%20the%20coming%20decades%20for%20our%20defence%20inventory%20management%2C%20alternative%20energy%20sources%20and%20for%20maintaining%20balance%20on%20the%20Eurasian%20continent.%20The%20Russia%20of%20the%20future%20will%20be%20very%20different%20from%20the%20Russia%20of%20the%20past%20%E2%80%93%20geopolitically%20relevant%20but%20economically%20weak.%20Russia%20is%20for%20India%20a%20permanent%20partner%20on%20the%20Eurasian%20continent%2C%20even%20though%20its%20perceived%20weakness%20will%20continue%20to%20invite%20US%20pinpricks%20in%20the%20coming%20decade.%20If%20the%20US%20%E2%80%93%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20powerful%20maritime%20power%20%E2%80%93%20places%20a%20low%20premium%20on%20stability%20on%20the%20Eurasian%20continent%2C%20India%20cannot%20remain%20insulated%20from%20its%20destabilizing%20impact%20for%20long.%20If%20the%20net%20result%20of%20US%20policy%20on%20the%20Eurasian%20continent%20is%20the%20steady%20expansion%20of%20Chinese%20influence%2C%20even%20while%20India%20is%20expected%20to%20join%20the%20US%20in%20containing%20China%20in%20the%20maritime%20domain%2C%20the%20resulting%20incongruity%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20grand%20strategy%20will%20be%20hard%20to%20ignore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20India%20must%20do%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20next%20decade%20will%20be%20more%20challenging%20than%20the%20last%20one.%20Diplomacy%20is%20important%20but%20there%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20national%20strength.%20The%20next%2025%20years%20is%20vital%20for%20our%20economic%20growth%2C%20ensuring%20equity%20and%20innovation%2C%20doubling%20our%20GDP%20every%20decade%20%E2%80%93%20aiming%20for%2030%20trillion%20USD%20GDP%20by%202047%20%E2%80%93%20is%20perhaps%20by%20itself%20the%20highest%20national%20security%20requirement.%20In%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20India%20has%20put%20in%20place%20transformative%20macroeconomic%20fundamentals%20%E2%80%93%20ranging%20from%20GST%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20domestic%20manufacturing%2C%20a%20world%20class%20digital%20public%20infrastructure%2C%20Start%20Ups%20to%20name%20a%20few.%20However%2C%20in%20the%20field%20of%20computing%20technology%2C%20which%20is%20the%20defining%20technology%20of%20this%20century%2C%20like%20nuclear%20technology%20was%20the%20yardstick%20of%20power%20last%20century%2C%20the%20US%20and%20China%20are%20the%20only%20two%20AI%20superpowers%20today.%20India%20is%20an%20insignificant%20computer%20power%2C%20even%20while%20considering%20our%20considerable%20talent%20in%20software%20design.%20While%20the%20Indian%20Government%20has%20initiated%20steps%20to%20catch%20up%2C%20we%20have%20a%20long%20way%20to%20go.%20India%20needs%20to%20be%20more%20than%20a%20data%20goldmine%20and%20software%20design%20sweatshop.%20We%20can%20and%20should%20be%20the%20front%20face%20of%20the%20front-end%20of%20the%20fourth%20Industrial%20revolution%2C%20not%20its%20back-end%20back%20office.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOverall%2C%20if%20we%20can%20maintain%20the%20tempo%20of%20reform%20and%20innovation%20under%20conditions%20of%20political%20and%20domestic%20stability%2C%20there%20is%20widespread%20expectation%20that%20%E2%80%98Incredible%E2%80%99%20India%20will%20also%20be%2C%20as%20some%20have%20said%20%E2%80%98Inevitable%E2%80%99%20India%20in%20terms%20of%20joining%20the%20ranks%20of%20the%20great%20powers.%20The%20road%20from%20aspiration%20to%20reality%20will%20have%20to%20be%20paved%20with%20unity%2C%20growth%2C%20innovation%2C%20and%20sacrifice%20over%20the%20coming%20decades.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20undergoing%20a%20quiet%20military%20revolution.%20Much%20delayed%20defence%20reforms%20now%20underway%20are%20being%20taken%20forward%20by%20the%20government%20in%20a%20determined%20way.%20Changes%20in%20command%20and%20control%2C%20with%20emphasis%20on%20jointness%2C%20integration%20and%20theaterisation%20will%20greatly%20enhance%20the%20combat%20capabilities%20of%20our%20armed%20forces.%20The%20indigenisation%20of%20procurement%20and%20domestic%20manufacture%20of%20weapon%20systems%20and%20greater%20participation%20of%20the%20private%20sector%20and%20emphasis%20on%20defence%20exports%20will%20fundamentally%20transform%20our%20armed%20forces.%20However%2C%20the%20most%20important%20change%20will%20be%20doctrinal%2C%20considering%20not%20only%20changes%20in%20our%20immediate%20security%20environment%20but%20also%20global%20trends%20which%20have%20been%20referred%20to.%20To%20support%20these%20changes%2C%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20increase%20defence%20spending%20to%20an%20average%20of%203%25%20of%20GDP%2C%20enshrined%20in%20law%2C%20for%20the%20next%20decade.%20This%20will%20provide%20a%20predictable%20resource%20base%20to%20plan%20this%20buildup.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20that%20it%20has%20not%20been%20done%20in%20the%20past-%20between%201963%20and%201988%20%E2%80%93%20India%E2%80%99s%20defence%20expenditure%20averaged%20above%203%25%20of%20GDP.%20Today%E2%80%99s%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20economic%20possibilities%2C%20its%20military%20modernisation%20programme%20and%20the%20troubled%20international%20security%20situation%20make%20this%20both%20possible%20and%20necessary.%20While%20conflict%20with%20China%20is%20not%20inevitable%2C%20a%20continuing%20gap%20in%20military%20capabilities%20will%20enhance%20the%20possibilities%20of%20conflict.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EGrammar%20of%20strategy%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20I%20conclude%2C%20let%20me%20reflect%20briefly%20on%20the%20status%20of%20strategic%20studies%20in%20India.%20As%20part%20of%20globalisation%2C%20it%20was%20understandable%20that%20our%20foreign%20policy%20and%20security%20communities%20readily%20absorbed%20strategic%20perspectives%20emanating%20from%20the%20West.%20Our%20expectations%20of%20a%20permanently%20benign%20global%20situation%20have%20been%20belied.%20This%20reversal%2C%20disappointing%20as%20it%20is%2C%20has%20also%20led%20to%20creeping%20self-doubt%20on%20whether%20we%20can%20afford%20to%20pursue%20a%20policy%20of%20strategic%20autonomy%2C%20when%20there%20is%20a%20growing%20power%20gap%20with%20China.%20The%20belief%20that%20some%20dilution%20of%20our%20strategic%20autonomy%20is%20a%20justifiable%20cost%20to%20be%20paid%20for%20its%20preservation%20is%20fundamentally%20flawed%20and%20can%20be%20a%20barrier%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20rise.%20Our%20strategic%20autonomy%20is%20both%20a%20practical%20requirement%20and%20a%20civilisational%20necessity%2C%20for%20no%20country%20has%20ever%20risen%20by%20fighting%20wars%20for%20other%20countries.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStrategic%20thought%20is%20not%20alien%20to%20India.%20Kautilya%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EArthshastra%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20not%20just%20a%20political%20treatise.%20It%20is%20not%20just%20a%20textbook%20on%20statecraft.%20It%20is%20a%20magnum%20opus%20on%20grand%20strategy%2C%20more%20comprehensive%20than%20the%20works%20of%20Machiavelli%2C%20Jomini%2C%20Clausewitz%20or%20other%20thinkers.%20Though%20written%20millennia%20ago%2C%20its%20timeless%20quality%20is%20derived%20from%20the%20grammar%20and%20logic%20that%20Kautilya%E2%80%99s%20distilled%20wisdom%20provides%20for%20strategy%E2%80%99s%20permanent%20dilemmas%20%E2%80%93%20how%20to%20pursue%20long%20term%20goals%20with%20constantly%20shifting%20balance%20of%20power%20amongst%20competing%20states%20under%20material%20limitations%20and%20mental%20distractions.%20Kautilya%E2%80%99s%20prescriptions%20are%20not%20for%20the%20fainthearted.%20They%20are%20for%20those%20wanting%20to%20transition%20India%20from%20power%20to%20great%20power%2C%20not%20for%20those%20willing%20to%20let%20India%20slip%20from%20partner%20to%20proxy.%20In%20Kautilya%E2%80%99s%20world%2C%20strategic%20autonomy%20is%20non-negotiable%2C%20as%20it%20is%20the%20original%20purpose%20for%20which%20the%20state%20exists.%20Kautilya%20is%20not%20just%20for%20a%20sharpening%20of%20the%20mind%20but%20also%20for%20a%20strengthening%20of%20the%20soul.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Arthshastra%20is%20a%20grammar%20of%20strategy%20for%20the%20ages%20with%20each%20age%20writing%20its%20own%20strategic%20literature%20relevant%20to%20its%20specific%20needs.%20With%20such%20a%20rich%20tradition%20to%20draw%20on%2C%20we%20should%20have%20no%20difficulty%20to%20construct%20our%20strategic%20thought%20and%20practice%20for%20India%E2%80%99s%20needs%20relevant%20to%20our%20times.%20This%20will%20entail%20restoring%20faith%20and%20confidence%20in%20ourselves%20and%20a%20clear%20vision%20of%20what%20we%20are%20and%20what%20we%20aspire%20to%20be%20%E2%80%93%20in%20other%20words%20to%20transition%20from%20an%20allotted%20identity%20given%20to%20us%20by%20others%20to%20an%20identity%20rooted%20in%20our%20land.%20In%20the%20world%20of%20strategy%2C%20what%20nations%20accomplish%20is%20determined%20by%20what%20they%20settle%20for%20as%20much%20as%20what%20they%20aspire%20to.%20For%20India%2C%20we%20owe%20to%20our%20sacred%20land%20the%20higher%20purpose%2C%20passion%2C%20and%20perseverance%20that%20is%20bequeathed%20by%20our%20civilisation%20%E2%80%93%20a%20vision%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20greatness%20that%20is%20backed%20by%20a%20moral%20conviction%20that%20provides%20all%20our%20people%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging%20and%20hope%20which%20soothes%20the%20pain%20of%20sacrifice%20our%20country%E2%80%99s%20rise%20will%20invariably%20require.%20It%20is%20to%20that%20higher%20calling%20that%20we%20must%20all%20strive%20for.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3ED.B.%20Venkatesh%20Varma%20is%20a%20former%20Indian%20diplomat%2C%20who%20served%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambassador%20to%20the%20Conference%20on%20Disarmament%2C%20Spain%20and%20the%20Russian%20Federation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704083457000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F01094845%2FScreenshot-2024-01-01-at-9.47.12.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-changing-world-russia-ukraine-nato%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ukraine%20is%20a%20tragic%20example%20of%20the%20fate%20that%20awaits%20those%20willing%20to%20become%20proxies%20in%20big%20power%20conflicts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-changing-world-russia-ukraine-nato%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22COMIC%3A%20I%20led%20an%20all-women%20military%20unit%20in%20Afghanistan.%20Here's%20what%20happened%20when%20Kabul%20fell.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22What%20Remains%20of%20Tomorrow%20FTP%203x4%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65923c5eab6f2ebb11f7fdc9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3E%EF%B9%92%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chaotic%20and%20abrupt%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbiden-speech-afghanistan-us-finalizes-withdrawal-2021-8%5C%22%3Ewithdrawal%20of%20American%20forces%20from%20Afghanistan%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20subsequent%20Taliban%20takeover%20caused%20massive%20upheaval%20in%20the%20country%2C%20particularly%20among%20those%20who%20spent%20much%20of%20the%20previous%20two%20decades%20workin