godman.%20Bajpayee%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%20combines%20in%20these%20moments%20fanboy%20awe%20and%20veneration%20for%20these%20legendary%20seniors%20with%20a%20brave%20and%20robust%20commitment%20to%20his%20calling%20and%20the%20righteousness%20of%20his%20cause.%20He%20is%20empathetic%20and%20supportive%20to%20the%20girl%2C%20and%20he%20does%20not%20flinch%20even%20after%20a%20series%20of%20key%20witnesses%20are%20murdered%20and%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20his%20life%20is%20in%20danger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIdealism%20is%20what%20also%20sustains%20the%20central%20protagonist%20in%20Vidhu%20Vinod%20Chopra%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3E12th%C2%A0Fail%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eanother%20exhilarating%20real-life%20story%20of%20a%20young%20man%20from%20a%20remote%20village%20in%20the%20Chambal%20region%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20(Manoj%20Kumar%20Sharma)%20who%20fights%20incredible%20odds%20to%20qualify%20finally%20in%20the%20most%20fiercely%20contested%20competitive%20examination%20in%20the%20country%20to%20become%20an%20IPS%20officer.%20As%20a%20young%20man%20he%20meets%20a%20police%20officer%20who%20is%20honest%2C%20kind%20and%20just.%20This%20encounter%20alters%20the%20course%20of%20his%20life.%20It%20is%20the%20dream%20to%20become%20a%20police%20officer%20like%20him%20that%20drives%20him%20to%20the%20city%2C%20where%20he%20survives%20through%20years%20of%20hard%20manual%20labour%2C%20disappointments%20and%20setbacks%20to%20study%20for%20the%20examination.%20He%20persists%20to%20rise%20again%20and%20again%20against%20defeat%20and%20hardship%2C%20to%20finally%20overcome.%20Vikram%20Massey%20brings%20a%20rare%20sensitivity%20and%20authenticity%20to%20his%20portrayal%2C%20raising%20him%20to%20the%20top%20rung%20of%20our%20actors.%20It%20is%20hard%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20to%20forget%20the%20sequence%20in%20the%20film%20when%20his%20friend%20tells%20him%20that%20he%20has%20qualified%20in%20the%20examination%2C%20and%20he%20just%20crumbles%20into%20a%20heap%20on%20the%20ground%20overcome%20with%20emotion.%20I%20wanted%20to%20stand%20up%20and%20cheer%20in%20a%20scene%20near%20the%20end%20when%2C%20Massey%E2%80%99s%20character%2C%20now%20a%20police%20officer%2C%20drives%20to%20a%20police%20station%20in%20Chambal%20to%20meet%20the%20policeman%20who%20years%20earlier%20had%20inspired%20him.%20The%20young%20officer%20touches%20his%20feet%2C%20the%20older%20man%20proudly%20salutes%20the%20man%20who%20is%20now%20his%20superior%20officer%2C%20and%20then%20they%20both%20embrace.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31115802%2Fdownload-19.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31115802%2Fdownload-19.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31115802%2Fdownload-19-300x123.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31115802%2Fdownload-19-1024x418.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691080%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22490%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%9912th%20Fail%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20am%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20police%20procedurals%2C%20less%20so%20when%20these%20are%20about%20serial%20killers.%20The%20reason%20why%20the%20web%20series%20%3Cem%3EDahaad%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Edirected%20by%20Reema%20Kagti%20and%20Ruchika%20Oberoi%2C%20still%20makes%20it%20to%20this%20list%20is%20because%20of%20its%20central%20character%2C%20a%20sub-inspector%20in%20a%20police%20station%20in%20a%20rural%20outpost%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20Anjali%20Bhaati%20(Sonakshi%20Sinha%20in%20a%20persuasive%20portrayal)%20and%20its%20realistic%20depiction%20of%20rural%20policing.%20Bhaati%20is%20a%20Dalit%20woman%2C%20and%20she%20is%20continuously%20reminded%20of%20this%20when%20she%20confronts%20people%20who%20wield%20the%20power%20of%20caste%2C%20class%20and%20patriarchy.%20In%20a%20particularly%20stirring%20gooseflesh-inducing%20sequence%2C%20when%20a%20dominant-caste%20landlord%20taunts%20and%20humiliates%20her%20as%20he%20blocks%20her%20entry%20to%20search%20his%20house%2C%20she%20forces%20her%20way%20in%20declaring%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Constitution%20gives%20me%20the%20power%20to%20enter%20your%20home%2C%20and%20you%20have%20no%20right%20to%20stop%20me.%E2%80%9D%20Memorable%20also%20are%20the%20final%20moments%20of%20the%20series%2C%20when%20Bhaati%20decides%20to%20change%20her%20surname%20to%20Meghwal.%20As%20Bhaati%2C%20her%20caste%20identity%20was%20ambiguous.%20As%20Meghwal%2C%20she%20is%20unmistakably%2C%20defiantly%20and%20proudly%20Dalit.%20%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22The%20Wire%20Recommends%3A%20Eight%20Movies%20We%20Watched%20and%20Liked%20This%20Year%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Ffilm%2Fthe-wire-recommends-movies%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%20Recommends%3A%20Eight%20Movies%20We%20Watched%20and%20Liked%20This%20Year%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20Dalit%20identity%20of%20another%20police%20officer%20that%20raises%20%3Cem%3EBheed%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ea%20searing%20documentation%20of%20the%20great%20migrant%20exodus%20that%20erupted%20after%20the%20Indian%20government%20imposed%20with%20four-hours%E2%80%99%20notice%20a%20punishing%20nation-wide%20lockdown.%20The%20police%20officer%20hides%20his%20Dalit%20identity%20with%20his%20upper-caste%20surname%2C%20Surya%20Kumar%20Singh.%20But%20his%20superior%20officer%20never%20fails%20to%20remind%20him%20of%20his%20caste.%20Singh%20is%20charged%20with%20blocking%20the%20movement%20of%20a%20crowd%20of%20migrants%20at%20a%20rural%20roadblock%20erected%20to%20prevent%20hundreds%20of%20starving%20workers%20desperate%20to%20return%20to%20their%20villages.%20The%20film%E2%80%99s%20director%20Anubhav%20Sinha%20deploys%20the%20range%20of%20characters%20heaving%20at%20the%20roadblock%20to%20depict%20how%20the%20fractures%20of%20class%2C%20caste%20and%20religious%20identity%20collapsed%20solidarities%20in%20this%20time%20of%20monumental%20disaster%20when%20people%20most%20needed%20to%20stand%20together.%20I%20bore%20first-hand%20witness%20to%20this%2C%20the%20greatest%20humanitarian%20crisis%20since%20Partition%2C%20and%20feel%20that%20Sinha%20falls%20short%20in%20reflecting%20the%20depth%20and%20range%20of%20the%20tragedy%20and%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20culpability%20of%20the%20state.%20But%20the%20film%20is%20strongest%20in%20its%20depiction%20of%20the%20Dalit%20police%20officer%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20own%20struggles%20as%20he%20comes%20to%20ultimately%20embrace%20both%20his%20identity%20and%20his%20inherent%20duty%20to%20stand%20firmly%20with%20the%20frantic%20stranded%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31120024%2Fbheed-movie-review-003.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31120024%2Fbheed-movie-review-003.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31120024%2Fbheed-movie-review-003-300x158.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F31120024%2Fbheed-movie-review-003-1024x538.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691081%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20still%20from%20%E2%80%98Bheed%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20in%20my%20list%20two%20significant%20films%20that%20directly%20confront%20the%20politics%20of%20hate%2C%20one%20in%20India%20and%20the%20other%20in%20neighbouring%20Bangladesh.%20The%20first%20of%20these%20is%20Sudhir%20Mishra%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EAfwaah%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20which%20Rahab%20Ahmad%2C%20a%20married%20Muslim%20CEO%20of%20a%20telecom%20country%20rescues%20a%20young%20Hindu%20woman%2C%20Nivedita%20as%20she%20is%20escaping%20from%20goons%20sent%20for%20her%20by%20her%20violent%20politician%20lover.%20The%20lives%20of%20both%20are%20endangered%20as%20Nivedita%E2%80%99s%20estranged%20lover%20manipulates%20social%20media%20to%20depict%20Rahab%20as%20a%20love%20jihadi%20who%20has%20fled%20with%20his%20Hindu%20lover.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHansal%20Mehta%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EFaraaz%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20gritty%20recreation%20of%20the%20terrorist%20attack%20by%20a%20group%20of%20five%20young%20Islamist%20terrorists%20on%20a%20caf%C3%A9%20in%20Dacca%20in%202016.%20The%20assault%20left%20dead%2029%20people%2C%20including%2020%20guests%20in%20the%20caf%C3%A9%2C%20caf%C3%A9%20staff%20and%20policepersons.%20The%20film%20tells%20the%20moving%20story%20of%2020-year-old%20Faraaz%20Ayaaz%20Hossein%2C%20the%20grandson%20of%20a%20leading%20business%20tycoon.%20The%20terrorists%20offer%20to%20let%20him%20walk%20out%20free%20because%20of%20his%20Muslim%20identity%2C%20but%20Faraaz%20refused%20to%20abandon%20his%20two%20friends%20to%20die%20in%20their%20hands%2C%20and%20as%20a%20result%20he%20also%20dies%20with%20them.%20Both%20films%20together%20depict%20the%20horrific%20visage%20of%20religious%20hatred%2C%20Hindu%20on%20one%20side%20of%20the%20border%20and%20Muslim%20on%20the%20other%2C%20but%20identical%20in%20many%20ways%20in%20their%20cruelty%20and%20mindless%20violence.%20But%20what%20both%20films%20also%20share%20in%20common%20is%20that%20when%20their%20central%20protagonists%20are%20endangered%20by%20the%20violence%20of%20hate%2C%20they%20choose%20even%20at%20the%20risk%20to%20their%20lives%20to%20hold%20fast%20t